cal):<\/strong> on a post-type archive the queried object is <code>WP_Post_Type<\/code> \u2014 not a term\/user \u2014 so the ladder falls to <code>get_the_ID()<\/code>, which WordPress points at the FIRST post of the archive's main query. Result: tags here read <em>Book Alpha's<\/em> rows (first in the loop), order-dependent. Elementor Pro's own ACF tags render empty in this context. The row picker enumerates from the NEWEST post of the previewed type (ties with the archive order are possible). For archive-level content, an options-page repeater is the intended tool.<\/p>","text_color":"#374151","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"size":14,"unit":"px"}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":false}]
